%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Asking%20the%20Fed%20to%20adjust%20its%20inflation%20target%20would%20be%20like%20waving%20a%20Pride%20flag%20at%20a%20DeSantis%20rally%2C%20Paul%20Krugman%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222176%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22paul%20krugman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e5f407912f290019a965ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221631%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENobel-winning%20economist%20Paul%20Krugman%3Cp%3EJeff%20Zelevansky%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPaul%20Krugman%20has%20long%20been%20a%20critic%20of%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20inflation%20target%2C%20and%20suggests%20the%20goal%20be%20bumped%20up%20to%203%25.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20central%20bankers'%20reaction%20to%20such%20suggestions%20is%20similar%20to%20what%20%26quot%3Byou'd%20get%20if%20you%20waved%20a%20Pride%20flag%20at%20a%20DeSantis%20rally%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20his%20New%20York%20Times%20op-ed%2C%20Krugman%20advocates%20for%20a%203%25%20target%20and%20to%20declare%20victory%20over%20inflation%20for%20good.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20raised%20interest%20rates%20at%20the%20fastest%20pace%20since%20the%201980s%20over%20the%20past%2016%20months%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20cool%20inflation%20down%20to%20its%20self-imposed%202%25%20target.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20top%20economist%20Paul%20Krugman%20sees%20that%20goal%20for%20price%20stability%20as%20a%20mistake%20%E2%80%93%20and%20urges%20central%20bankers%20to%20swallow%20their%20pride%20and%20update%20the%20metric.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20if%20the%202%20percent%20target%20was%20probably%20a%20mistake%2C%20and%20if%20we%20could%20do%20it%20over%20again%2C%20we'd%20probably%20go%20for%203%2C%20why%20not%20just%20declare%20victory%20over%20inflation%20today%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F22%2Fopinion%2Finflation-target-fed-economy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20an%20op-ed%20for%20the%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrugman%20even%20took%20a%20jab%20at%20Florida%20governor%20Ron%20DeSantis%20to%20get%20his%20point%20across.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOK%2C%20I've%20been%20in%20meetings%20with%20current%20and%20former%20central%20bankers%2C%20and%20the%20reaction%20you%20get%20if%20you%20suggest%20accepting%20current%20inflation%20and%20revising%20the%20target%20accordingly%20is%20more%20or%20less%20the%20reaction%20I%20imagine%20you'd%20get%20if%20you%20waved%20a%20Pride%20flag%20at%20a%20DeSantis%20rally%20(although%20you're%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20beaten%20up%20or%20shot).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20Krugman%20has%20called%20for%20a%203%25%20inflation%20target.%20Earlier%20this%20week%2C%20he%20made%20a%20case%20for%20the%20same%20in%20a%20post%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpaulkrugman%2Fstatus%2F1693597491030090195%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20op-ed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20agree%20with%20Jason%20Furman's%20call%20for%20a%203%25%20inflation%20target%20%E2%80%94%20the%20rationale%20for%202%25%20has%20been%20overtaken%20by%20a%20couple%20of%20decades'%20experience%20(and%20many%20of%20us%20have%20been%20saying%20this%20for%20a%20while)%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-mohamed-el-erian-fed-inflation-target-powell-speech-2023-8%5C%22%3EBut%20economist%20Mohamed%20El-Erian%20disagrees%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20warning%20there's%20no%20chance%20the%20Fed%20will%20calibrate%20its%20inflation%20target%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20a%20strong%20argument.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20hard%20for%20a%20central%20bank%20to%20change%20an%20inflation%20target%20when%20it%20has%20been%20missing%20it%20so%20consistently%2C%26quot%3B%20El-Erian%20told%20CNBC%20on%20Monday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20yes%2C%20there's%20a%20theoretical%20argument%20for%20a%20higher%20inflation%20target%2C%20but%20don't%20look%20for%20chair%20Powell%20to%20touch%20that%20issue%20in%20any%20significant%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20economists'%20comments%20come%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell's%20speech%20at%20the%202023%20Jackson%20Hole%20Economic%20Symposium%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-fed-inflation-target-pride-flag-desantis-rally-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692800712000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e5f407912f290019a965ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-fed-inflation-target-pride-flag-desantis-rally-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Central%20bankers'%20reactions%20to%20suggestions%20for%20a%20higher%20inflation%20target%20is%20similar%20to%20what%20%26quot%3Byou'd%20get%20if%20you%20waved%20a%20Pride%20flag%20at%20a%20DeSantis%20rally%2C%26quot%3B%20Krugman%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jwilkins%40insider.com%20(Joseph%20Wilkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-fed-inflation-target-pride-flag-desantis-rally-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20reasons%20why%20investors%20should%20buy%20stocks%20now%20ahead%20of%20Nvidia%20earnings%20and%20Powell's%20Jackson%20Hole%20speech%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Powell%20Jackson%20Hole%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e5fbd8912f290019a96a08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFederal%20Reserve%20policymakers%20including%20chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20meet%20in%20Jackson%20Hole%20this%20week.%3Cp%3EAmber%20Baesler%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EInvestors%20should%20buy%20stocks%20ahead%20of%20Nvidia's%20earnings%20report%20and%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell's%20speech%20at%20Jackson%20Hole.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bold%20call%20comes%20from%20Fundstrat's%20Tom%20Lee%2C%20who%20offered%20four%20reasons%20why%20he%20expects%20stocks%20to%20rise%20soon.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20rates%20could%20be%20pushing%20higher%2C%20equities%20are%20showing%20early%20signs%20of%20diverging%20from%20higher%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20tough%20few%20weeks%20for%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20with%20both%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fnasdaq_100%5C%22%3ENasdaq%20100%3C%2Fa%3E%20down%20about%205%25%20in%20August%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsinsight.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFundstrat's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Tom%20Lee%20sees%20a%20buying%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20note%20to%20clients%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Lee%20said%20today%20is%20the%20day%20to%20add%20risk%20to%20portfolios%20and%20buy%20stocks%20ahead%20of%20two%20big%20market-moving%20events%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fnvda-stock%5C%22%3ENvidia's%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fnvidia-earnings-preview-q2-wall-street-nvda-stock-artificial-intelligence-2023-8%5C%22%3Eearnings%20report%20after%20the%20market%20close%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell's%20speech%20at%20the%20Jackson%20Hole%20Symposium%20Friday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bold%20call%20comes%20amid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-hike-july-inflation-powell-recession-federal-reserve-2023-7%5C%22%3Ea%20surge%20in%20interest%20rates%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20the%2010-year%20US%20Treasury%20yield%20surged%2050%20basis%20points%20over%20the%20past%20few%20weeks%20to%20levels%20not%20seen%20since%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20this%20rise%20in%20rates%2C%20we%20believe%20probabilities%20have%20shifted%20to%20favor%20stocks%20being%20higher%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20That%20is%2C%20we%20would%20be%20buyers%20of%20equities%20starting%20Wednesday%2C%20even%20if%20we%20are%20only%20in%20'close%20proximity'%20to%20a%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20four%20reasons%20why%20now%20is%20the%20time%20to%20buy%20stocks%2C%20right%20before%20two%20big%20market-shaking%20events%2C%20according%20to%20Fundstrat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1.%20Stocks%20typically%20do%20well%20after%20Jackson%20Hole.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20analyzed%20market%20performance%20in%20the%20week%20after%20Jackson%20Hole%20speeches%2C%20and%20found%20that%20stocks%20typically%20move%20higher%2C%20not%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20analysis%20suggests%20there%20is%20a%20greater%20than%2080%25%20%5Bchance%5D%20equities%20rally%20post-Friday%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20at%20data%20since%202003%2C%20Lee%20found%20seven%20instances%20in%20which%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20was%20down%20in%20the%20two%20weeks%20prior%20to%20the%20Fed%20speech%2C%20similar%20to%20what%20the%20current%20stock%20market%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20six%20of%20those%20seven%20instances%2C%20stocks%20gained%20in%20the%20week%20after%20Jackson%20Hole%20by%200.5%25-5%25.%20One%20exception%20was%20last%20year%2C%20when%20Powell%20was%20especially%20hawkish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20context%20is%20different%20in%202023%2C%20as%20inflation%20is%20not%20only%20on%20a%20glide%20path%20lower%2C%20but%20the%20surge%20in%2010-year%20yields%20threatens%20a%20potentially%20greater%20tightening%20of%20financial%20conditions%20and%20thus%2C%20we%20see%20probabilities%20favoring%20language%20addressing%20this%20surge%20in%20yields%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20New%20data%20could%20put%20pressure%20on%20inflation.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20data%20show%20pay%20for%20new%20hires%20declined%20versus%20a%20year%20ago.%20Meanwhile%2C%20auto-loan%20delinquencies%20are%20up%2C%20likely%20putting%20pressure%20on%20car%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20previously%20wrote%20how%20used%20car%20prices%20could%20fall%20another%2030%25%20from%20here.%20All%20of%20this%20argues%20for%20future%20inflation%20to%20be%20softer%20and%20for%20Fed%20path%20to%20turn%20dovish%20sooner%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E3.%20Stocks%20are%20diverging%20from%20rates.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20interest%20rates%20surged%20earlier%20this%20week%20to%20their%20highest%20level%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20technology%20stocks%20actually%20moved%20higher%2C%20not%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20somewhat%20important%20development%2C%20if%20this%20is%20due%20to%20stocks%20sensing%20rates%20are%20about%20to%20roll%20over.%20Our%20view%20is%20a%20calculated%20bet%20that%20stocks%20are%20rising%2C%20despite%20higher%20rates%2C%20because%20the%20stock%20market%20is%20sensing%20this%20turn%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20saying%20the%20last%20push%20higher%20in%20rates%20will%20not%20proportionately%20hit%20stocks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E4.%20Upcoming%20data%20could%20ease%20inflation%20concerns.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20economic%20data%20is%20due%20next%20week%2C%20including%20Case-Shiller%20Home%20prices%2C%20job%20openings%2C%20and%20