%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%20by%20journalist%20Gagan%20Kohli%2C%20a%20team%20of%20approximately%2012-15%20highly%20skilled%20Indian%20soldiers%20allegedly%20crossed%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LoC)%20into%20the%20Pakistani-administered%20Kashmir%20region%20near%20Kotli.%20The%20mission%20purportedly%20aimed%20to%20neutralise%20a%20terrorist%20camp%20responsible%20for%20fomenting%20unrest%20and%20planning%20infiltration%20attempts%20into%20Indian%20territory.%20The%20report%20claims%20that%20seven%20to%20eight%20terrorists%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20operation%2C%20and%20four%20launching%20pads%20were%20destroyed.%20It%20also%20shows%20a%20graphic%20representation%20of%20the%20LoC%20and%20four%20tent-like%20structures%20that%20were%20purportedly%20destroyed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKohli%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20paints%20a%20vivid%20picture%20of%20the%20mission%E2%80%99s%20success%2C%20highlighting%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Indian%20soldiers%2C%20unscathed%2C%20and%20reiterating%20their%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20safeguarding%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20borders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20these%20claims%20were%20met%20with%20swift%20denial%20from%20authorities.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20fact-checking%20body%2C%20the%20PIB%20Fact%20Check%2C%20said%20the%20report%20is%20false%20and%20baseless.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22hi%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJagranNews%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40JagranNews%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%88%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF%20%E0%A4%AD%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A4%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5