E%3Cstrong%3EBig%20brands%20like%20Bud%20Light%20and%20Target%20have%20been%20in%20the%20news%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrands-brace-for-right-wing-war-on-pride-month-lgbtq-2023-6%5C%22%3Ebacklash%20for%20supporting%20social%20issues.%3C%2Fa%3E%20How%20should%20brands%20handle%20supporting%20social%20issues%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20problem%20often%20is%20that%20companies%20have%20great%20communications%20and%20marketing%20teams%20but%20they%20don't%20have%20teams%20that%20are%20skilled%20on%20issues.%20And%20if%20they%20do%2C%20they%20often%20have%20someone%20from%20one%20party%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20team%20of%20both%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20put%20together%20people%20who%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20politics%20from%20the%20Democrat%20and%20Republican%20sides%20with%20polling%20and%20financial%20communications%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20cookie-cutter%20answer%20to%20these%20questions.%20It%20depends%20on%20your%20mix%20of%20stakeholders%2C%20your%20values%20as%20a%20company%2C%20and%20what%20you%20do%20and%20do%20not%20stand%20for.%20People%20hate%20Johnny-come-latelys%20who%20suddenly%20decide%20to%20virtue%20signal%20on%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20potential%20exposure%20for%20people%20who%20do%20that.%20The%20biggest%20problem%20is%20that%20%5Bcompanies%5D%20don't%20have%20a%20balanced%20group%20of%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20companies%20never%20like%20to%20spend%20on%20this%20until%20there's%20a%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20recently%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prnewswire.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fstagwells-stgw-constellation-network-acquires-fast-growing-tinsel-experiential-design-301879703.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebought%20the%20experiential%20design%20studio%20Tinsel%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20amount.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20other%20acquisitions%20are%20you%20interested%20in%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20topic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fagency-executives-leading-advertisers-charge-into-generative-ai-2023-3%5C%22%3Edu%20jour%20is%20AI.%3C%2Fa%3E%20There's%20obviously%20a%20lot%20of%20clients%20who%20want%20to%20know%20how%20they%20incorporate%20AI%20in%20their%20marketing%2C%20and%20I%20think%20this%20will%20generate%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20for%20digital-transformation%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20building%20a%20suite%20of%20tech%20products.%20We%20have%20PRophet%20%E2%80%94%20we'll%20help%20you%20write%20news%20releases%2C%20see%20who's%20going%20to%20be%20interested%20in%20it%2C%20write%20the%20pitches%2C%20and%20send%20the%20pitches%20out%20%5Busing%20AI%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20first%20thing%20that%20you%20have%20to%20be%20cognizant%20of%20is%20that%20we're%20used%20to%20people%20interacting%20with%20links%20that%20they%20click%20on%20%E2%80%94%20generative%20AI%20changes%20the%20whole%20way%20that%20one%20interacts%20with%20technology%20and%20how%20one%20is%20marketed%20to.%20We're%20all%20used%20to%20clicking%20on%20links%20%E2%80%94%20now%20we%20can%20get%20a%20response%20and%20we%20can%20then%20have%20follow-up%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20obvious%20production%20enhancements%20and%20storyboard%20making%2C%20but%20the%20biggest%20impact%20%5Bof%20AI%5D%20is%20once%20you%20begin%20to%20incorporate%20it%20into%20the%20work%20itself.%20I%20don't%20think%20people%20are%20spending%20enough%20time%20or%20thinking%20about%20that%20as%20the%20fundamental%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-penn-talks-ai-brands-supporting-social-issues-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692797218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64be