B%22title%22%3A%22Chandrayaan-3's%20Lander%20Has%20Touched%20Down%20On%20Moon.%20Over%20To%20Rover%20Pragyan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELander%20Vikram's%20final%20touchdown%C2%A0speed%20was%20well%20within%20its%20safe%20limits.%20Four%20engines%20ran%20initially.%20Two%20of%20them%20were%20shut%20down%20later%2C%20so%20the%20touchdown%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20was%20powered%20by%20two%20engines.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELander%20Vikram%20kicked%20up%20a%20large%20cloud%20of%20Moon%20dust%20when%20it%20landed.%20The%20dust%20will%20not%20settle%20down%20anytime%20soon%20due%20to%20the%20extremely%20weak%20gravitational%20force%20the%20Moon%20exerts%2C%20but%20will%20scatter%20away%20on%20its%20own%20momentum.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20rover%20Pragyan%20will%20emerge%20from%20the%20lander%20three-and-a-half%20hours%20after%20lander%20Vikram%20touched%20down%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20near%20the%20Moon's%20South%20Pole.%20India%20is%20the%20first%20country%20to%20land%20a%20spacecraft%20near%20the%20lunar%20South%20Pole.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20did%20not%20want%20the%20fine%20Moon%20dust%20to%20coat%20the%20cameras%20and%20other%20sensitive%20instruments%2C%20so%20it%20decided%20to%20wait%20for%20over%20three%20hours%20to%20ensure%20the%20dust%20moves%20away%20from%20the%20lander%20Vikram.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20rover%20Pragyan%20will%20first%20extend%20its%20solar%20arrays%20and%20roll%20out%20with%20a%20wire%20connected%20to%20the%20lander%20Vikram.%20The%20wire%20will%20be%20snapped%20once%20the%20rover%20is%20stable%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%20It%20will%20then%20start%20its%20scientific%20mission.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692796500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F4sbf28l_lander-vikram_625x300_23_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-lander-vikram-on-moon-now-whats