Chandrayaan-3's%20Vikram%20lander%20began%20landing%2C%20the%20legion%20of%20scientists%20at%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20triggered%20the%20'power%20descent'%20phase%2C%20which%20referred%20to%20an%20automated%20landing%20sequence%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20lander%20with%20no%20help%20from%20Mission%20Control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EChandrayaan-3's%20Automated%20Landing%20Sequence%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20'power%20descent'%20phase%20consists%20of%20four%20stages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20the%20%3Cstrong%3E'rough%20braking'%20phase%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20which%20reduces%20the%20Vikram%20lander's%20horizontal%20speed%20from%201.68%20km%20per%20second%20(over%206%2C000%20km%20per%20hour)%20to%20nearly%20zero.%20This%20is%20a%20critical%20phase%20since%20the%20lander%20must%20scrub%20high%20speeds%20in%20a%20very%20short%20space%20of%20time%20to%20ensure%20a%20perfect%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EVIDEO%20%7C%20Chandrayaan-3%3A%20The%20rough%20braking%2C%20which%20is%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20power%20descent%2C%20is%20underway.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FChandrayaan3%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Chandrayaan3%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FChandrayaan3Landing%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Chandrayaan3Landing%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FISRO%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23ISRO%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FzFSPc0aNpb%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FzFSPc0aNpb%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20(%40PTI_News)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1694325777389515114%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2023%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20the%20%3Cstrong%3E'attitude%20hold'%20phase%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20which%20lasts%20for%20around%2010%20seconds%20only.%20In%20this%20phase%20the%20Vikram%20lander%20remains%20at%20a%20pre-set%20altitude%20of%207.42%20km%20while%20it%20begins%20to%20tilt%20from%20a%20horizontal%20to%20vertical%20position.%20In%20this%20phase%20the%20spacecraft%20covers%20around%203.48%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELIVE%20COVERAGE%20%7C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-moon-landing-live-isro-vikram-lander-to-land-on-moon-today-4320838%5C%22%3EIndia%20Makes%20History%2C%20Becomes%204th%20Nation%20To%20Land%20On%20Moon%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20phase%20is%20the%20%3Cstrong%3E'fine%20braking'%20phase%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20this%20is%20the%20longest%20of%20the%20four%2C%20lasting%20over%20175%20seconds.%20In%20this%20phase%20Vikram%20lander%20will%20travel%20the%20final%2028-odd%20km%20to%20the%20Moon's%20surface%20while%20continuing%20to%20manouvre%20into%20an%20upright%20position.%20The%20'nominal%20speed'%20at%20this%20time%20is%20zero%20metres%20per%20second%20and%20the%20altitude%20will%20come%20down%20to%20around%20800-1000%20metres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20it%20was%20in-between%20the%20second%20and%20third%20phases%20Chandrayaan-2%20crashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20phase%20is%20the%20%3Cstrong%3E'terminal%20descent'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20in%20which%20the%20lander%20travels%20the%20final%20few%20hundred%20metres%20to%20the%20Moon's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-lands-on-moon-india-joins-elite-space-club-4322798%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_bigstory%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia's%20Chandrayaan-3%20Lights%20Up%20Dark%20Side%20Of%20The%20Moon%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EChandrayaan-3%20On%20The%20Moon.%20What%20Next%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20Chandrayaan-