ent%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fchandrayaan-3-pragyan-to-roll-out-soon%2Farticleshow%2F102988746.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chandrayaan-3%3A%20Vikram%20Lander%20Successfully%20Achieves%20Soft%20Landing%20on%20Moon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23175921%2FScreenshot-2023-08-23-at-5.58.50-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAfter%20a%20journey%20through%20space%20of%20a%20month%20and%20nine%20days%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Chandrayaan-3%20succeeded%20in%20its%20primary%20mission%20of%20achieving%20a%20historic%20soft%20landing%20in%20the%20Moon%E2%80%99s%20south%20pole%20region%20at%206%3A03%20pm%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20August%2023.%20Chandrayaan-3%E2%80%99s%20successful%20soft%20landing%20makes%20India%20only%20the%20fourth%20country%20to%20do%20so%20on%20the%20Moon%E2%80%99s%20surface%20and%20the%20first%20to%20do%20so%20near%20its%20south%20pole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fchandrayaan-3-mission-launch-successful%5C%22%3Elaunched%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20July%2014%20from%20the%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Sriharikota.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chandrayaan%20programme%20for%20lunar%20exploration%20was%20first%20announced%20by%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%202003.%20Chandrayaan-1%20was%20launched%20in%202008%20%E2%80%93%20and%20successfully%20completed%20its%20mission%20of%20crash%20landing%20a%20probe%20on%20the%20Moon%E2%80%99s%20surface%20%E2%80%93%20when%20Manmohan%20Singh%20was%20prime%20minister.%20The%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%E2%80%99s%20plans%20for%20Chandrayaan-2%20got%20delayed%20because%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20provide%20a%20lander%20in%20time%20so%20the%20project%20was%20recast%20to%20envisage%20India%20building%20the%20lander%20on%20its%20own.%20When%20launched%20eventually%20in%202019%2C%20Chandrayaan-2%20was%20unable%20to%20make%20the%20planned%20soft%20landing%20%E2%80%93%20a%20task%20ISRO%20achieved%20with%20Chandrayaan-3.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.isro.gov.in%2FChandrayaan3_New.html%5C%22%3Eseveral%20improvements%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20its%20predecessor.%20ISRO%20has%20increased%20the%20intended%20landing%20zone%20to%204.2%20km%20long%20and%202.5%20km%20wide%2C%20meaning%20the%20spacecraft%20has%20a%20higher%20margin%20of%20error.%20Chandrayaan-3%20also%20has%20four%20engines%20with%20adjustable%20throttle%20and%20orientation%20and%20a%20Laser%20Doppler%20Velocimeter%20to%20control%20its%20altitude%20and%20orientation%20in%20all%20phases%20of%20descent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesnownews.com%2Ftechnology-science%2Fchandrayaan-3s-vikram-lander-set-to-detach-today-why-is-it-crucial-article-102791293%5C%22%3EVikram%20lander%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself%20has%20more%20sensitive%20instruments%20than%20those%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FUTOJHl9aQCI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScientific%20payload%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20rover%2C%20Chandrayaan-3%20also%20has%20scientific%20payload%20like%20the%20Spectro-polarimetry%20of%20Habitable%20Planet%20Earth%20(SHAPE)%2C%20which%20will%20study%20the%20spectral%20and%20polarimetric%20measurements%20of%20Earth%20from%20the%20lunar%20orbit.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Faerospace%2Fwhy-lunar-touchdown-offers-real-payoff-for-india%2F%5C%22%3Emission%20will%20also%20insert%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20thermal%20probe%2010%20cm%20into%20the%20lunar%20surface%20to%20measure%20the%20temperature%20gradient.%20This%20will%20help%20improve%20the%20knowledge%20of%20stability%20zones%20for%20resources%20like%20frozen%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Vikram%20lander%E2%80%99s%20six-wheeled%20lunar%20rover%2C%20called%20Pragyan%2C%20is%20carrying%20two%20payloads%3A%20an%20Alpha%20Particle%20X-Ray%20Spectrometer%20and%20a%20Laser%20Induced%20Breakdown%20Spectroscope%20to%20measure%20the%20composition%20of%20lunar%20rocks%20and%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20instruments%20were%20used%20by%20the%20China%20National%20Space%20Administration%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.1088%2F1674-4527%2F14%2F12%2F008%2Fmeta%5C%22%3EYutu%20rovers%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%20Pragyan%20will%20explore%20new%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Faerospace%2Fwhy-lunar-touchdown-offers-real-payoff-for-india%2F%5C%22%3EWhy%20Lunar%20Touchdown%20Offers%20Real%20Payoff%20for%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EModi%20addresses%20scientists%20after%20landing%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20already%20considerable%20public%20interest%20in%20the%20impending%20landing%2C%20with%20wall-to-wall%20media%20coverage%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20going%20the%20extra%20mile%20to%20ensure%20a%20captive%20audience%20for%20an%20event%20that%20is%20being%20seen%20by%20it%20as%20a%20great%20PR%20and%20political%20opportunity%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fchandrayaan-3-launch-another-achievement-under-pm-modi-s-leadership-says-guj-cm-news-302929%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20BJP%20leaders%20describing%20the%20mission%20as%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cone%20more%2